Package: phytometr
Title: Power Analysis and Experimental Design for Host–Environment–Holobiont Studies
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Felix", "Zimmermann", 
           email = "felix.zimmermann@wsl.ch",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-0762-2454"))
Description: 
    A simulation framework for designing and evaluating experiments on 
    host–environment–holobiont systems. The package provides tools for defining 
    environmental gradients, modelling clonal or natural host systems, and 
    simulating holobiont responses (e.g., diversity, abundance, composition). 
    Users can perform statistically grounded power analyses to determine the 
    environmental variation and replication required to detect environmental, 
    host, or interaction effects on holobiont components. A flexible 
    literature-based parameterisation allows modelling component sensitivity 
    to environmental drivers. A later development phase will extend the framework 
    to full genotype–environment association simulations using coalescent models.
